{
  "stem": "7506.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The appellplatz was in the middle of the part of the camp of the Sternlager, where we were, opposite a gate-- not the main gate of the whole of Belsen, but a gate into the Sternlager from the rest of the camp, which I could always see quite plainly.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we'd have to stand in appell five in a row.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Always five.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The men and the women separate.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I would be with my father and my uncle.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I always remember the up and down.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They come and walk up and down, up and down, with always a list.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So many times, counting and come back again, and come back, and then go and talk to a higher officer, and come back again.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And as a child with little patience, rather had been playing than standing there in the freezing cold, we would stand there and the men would talk in whisper tones to each other until they noticed that the person, the SS [? that ?] coming nearer.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They would always use like, a Dutch Jewish word.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't really know what it means.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I know what it implies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they would say [SPEAKING DUTCH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that means shut up, be quiet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They would come again to count.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And at times, we'd be standing there hours, hours.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They'd even go away and leave us standing there and come back again.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And because it was cold, we always used to do like that, hitting ourselves with our own arms to keep warm.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Never being able to leave the place, freezing cold.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Even if it was raining, we were standing there, standing there, standing there, which seemed to be hours and hours.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Whether in actual fact each time it was hours, I don't really know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It certainly seemed like hours.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
